			"text": "Fulmenocursor tevax comes from the Early Cretaceous, with fossils found in the Crato Formation, Brazil. It is a small scutigerid, growing up to only 1 cm in length, possibly more. It is currently the earliest known member of its family Scutigeridae. The generic name derives from the Latin words 'fulmen', to mean 'lightening'; and 'cursor', to mean 'runner'. The specific name derives from the Latin word 'tenax', to mean 'tenacious'."
